{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"For the last 20 years I've been designing puzzles."},{"time":4000,"text":"And I'm here today to give you"},{"time":9000,"text":"a little tour, starting from the very first puzzle I designed,"},{"time":11000,"text":"through what I'm doing now."},{"time":13000,"text":"I've designed puzzles for books, printed things."},{"time":16000,"text":"I'm the puzzle columnist for Discover Magazine."},{"time":18000,"text":"I've been doing that for about 10 years."},{"time":20000,"text":"I have a monthly puzzle calendar."},{"time":22000,"text":"I do toys. The bulk of my work is in computer games."},{"time":25000,"text":"I did puzzles for \"Bejeweled.\""},{"time":27000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":28000,"text":"I didn't invent \"Bejeweled.\" I can't take credit for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"So, very first puzzle,"},{"time":33000,"text":"sixth grade, my teacher said,"},{"time":35000,"text":"\"Oh, let's see, that guy, he likes to make stuff."},{"time":37000,"text":"I'll have him cut out letters out of construction paper"},{"time":40000,"text":"for the board.\""},{"time":43000,"text":"I thought this was a great assignment."},{"time":45000,"text":"And so here is what I came up with. I start fiddling with it."},{"time":48000,"text":"I came up with this letter. This is a letter of the alphabet"},{"time":51000,"text":"that's been folded just once."},{"time":53000,"text":"The question is, which letter is it if I unfold it?"},{"time":58000,"text":"One hint: It's not \"L.\""},{"time":60000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":62000,"text":"It could be an \"L,\" of course."},{"time":64000,"text":"So, what else could it be?"},{"time":66000,"text":"Yeah, a lot of you got it."},{"time":69000,"text":"Oh yeah. So, clever thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"Now, that was my first puzzle. I got hooked."},{"time":74000,"text":"I created something new, I was very excited"},{"time":78000,"text":"because, you know, I'd made crossword puzzles,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but that's sort of like filling in somebody else's matrix."},{"time":83000,"text":"This was something really original. I got hooked."},{"time":85000,"text":"I read Martin Gardner's columns in Scientific American."},{"time":88000,"text":"Went on, and eventually decided to devote myself, full time, to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"Now, I should pause and say, what do I mean by puzzle?"},{"time":95000,"text":"A puzzle is a problem that is fun to solve"},{"time":98000,"text":"and has a right answer."},{"time":100000,"text":"\"Fun to solve,\" as opposed to everyday problems,"},{"time":104000,"text":"which, frankly, are not very well-designed puzzles."},{"time":107000,"text":"You know, they might have a solution."},{"time":109000,"text":"It might take a long time. Nobody wrote down the rules clearly."},{"time":112000,"text":"Who designed this?"},{"time":114000,"text":"It's like, you know, life is not a very well-written story"},{"time":116000,"text":"so we have to hire writers to make movies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"Well, I take everyday problems, and I make puzzles out of them."},{"time":122000,"text":"And \"right answer,\" of course there might be more than one right answer;"},{"time":125000,"text":"many puzzles have more than one."},{"time":127000,"text":"But as opposed to a couple other forms of play,"},{"time":129000,"text":"toys and games --"},{"time":131000,"text":"by toy I mean, something you play with that doesn't have a particular goal."},{"time":134000,"text":"You can create one out of Legos."},{"time":136000,"text":"You know, you can do anything you want."},{"time":138000,"text":"Or competitive games like chess where,"},{"time":141000,"text":"well, you're not trying to solve ... You can make a chess puzzle,"},{"time":144000,"text":"but the goal really is to beat another player."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"I consider that puzzles are an art form."},{"time":151000,"text":"They're very ancient. It goes back as long as there is written history."},{"time":154000,"text":"It's a very small form, like a joke,"},{"time":156000,"text":"a poem, a magic trick or a song, very compact form."},{"time":160000,"text":"At worst, they're throwaways, they're for amusement."},{"time":163000,"text":"But at best they can reach for something more"},{"time":166000,"text":"and create a memorable impression."},{"time":168000,"text":"The progression of my career that you'll see"},{"time":170000,"text":"is looking for creating puzzles that have a memorable impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"So, one thing I found early on, when I started doing computer games,"},{"time":177000,"text":"is that I could create puzzles that will alter your perception."},{"time":180000,"text":"I'll show you how. Here is a famous one."},{"time":183000,"text":"So, it's two profiles in black, or a white vase in the middle."},{"time":186000,"text":"This is called a figure-ground illusion."},{"time":188000,"text":"The artist M.C. Escher exploited that"},{"time":190000,"text":"in some of his wonderful prints."},{"time":192000,"text":"Here we have \"Day and Night.\""},{"time":194000,"text":"Here is what I did with figure and ground."},{"time":202000,"text":"So, here we have \"figure\" in black."},{"time":204000,"text":"Here we have \"figure\" in white."},{"time":206000,"text":"And it's all part of the same design."},{"time":209000,"text":"The background to one is the other."},{"time":211000,"text":"Originally I tried to do the words \"figure\" and \"ground.\""},{"time":213000,"text":"But I couldn't do that, I realized. I changed the problem."},{"time":216000,"text":"It's all \"figure.\""},{"time":218000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"A few other things. Here is my name."},{"time":223000,"text":"And that turns into the title of my first book, \"Inversions.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"These sorts of designs now go by the word \"ambigram.\""},{"time":232000,"text":"I'll show you just a couple others. Here we have"},{"time":234000,"text":"the numbers one through 10, the digits zero through nine, actually."},{"time":237000,"text":"Each letter here is one of these digits."},{"time":240000,"text":"Not strictly an ambigram in the conventional sense."},{"time":243000,"text":"I like pushing on what an ambigram can mean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"Here's the word \"mirror.\" No, it's not the same upside-down."},{"time":248000,"text":"It's the same this way."},{"time":252000,"text":"And a marvelous fellow from the Media Lab"},{"time":254000,"text":"who just got appointed head of RISD, is John Maeda."},{"time":258000,"text":"And so I did this for him. It's sort of a visual canon."},{"time":262000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":265000,"text":"And recently in Magic magazine"},{"time":270000,"text":"I've done a number of ambigrams on magician's names."},{"time":272000,"text":"So here we have Penn and Teller, same upside-down."},{"time":277000,"text":"This appears in my puzzle calendar."},{"time":280000,"text":"Okay, let's go back to the slides."},{"time":282000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Now, those are fun to look at."},{"time":286000,"text":"Now how would you do it interactively?"},{"time":289000,"text":"For a while I was an interface designer."},{"time":291000,"text":"And so I think a lot about interaction."},{"time":293000,"text":"Well, let's first of all simplify the vases illusion,"},{"time":295000,"text":"make the thing on the right."},{"time":297000,"text":"Now, if you could pick up the black vase,"},{"time":299000,"text":"it would look like the figure on top."},{"time":301000,"text":"If you could pick up the white area,"},{"time":303000,"text":"it would look like the figure on the bottom."},{"time":305000,"text":"Well, you can't do that physically,"},{"time":307000,"text":"but on a computer you can do it. Let's switch over to the P.C."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"And here it is, figure-ground."},{"time":313000,"text":"The goal here is to take the pieces on the left"},{"time":316000,"text":"and make them so they look like the shape on the right."},{"time":319000,"text":"And this follows the rules I just said:"},{"time":321000,"text":"any black area that is surrounded by white can be picked up."},{"time":324000,"text":"But that is also true of any white area."},{"time":326000,"text":"So, here we got the white area in the middle,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and you can pick it up."},{"time":330000,"text":"I'll just go one step further."},{"time":332000,"text":"So, here is --"},{"time":334000,"text":"here is a couple pieces. Move them together,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and now this is an active piece."},{"time":339000,"text":"You can really get inside somebody's perception"},{"time":341000,"text":"and have them experience something."},{"time":343000,"text":"It's like the old maxim of"},{"time":345000,"text":"\"you can tell somebody something"},{"time":347000,"text":"and show them, but if they do it they really learn it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"Here is another thing you can do."},{"time":351000,"text":"There is a game called Rush Hour."},{"time":353000,"text":"This is one of the true masterpieces in puzzle design"},{"time":355000,"text":"besides Rubik's cube."},{"time":357000,"text":"So, here we have a crowded parking lot"},{"time":359000,"text":"with cars all over the place."},{"time":361000,"text":"The goal is to get the red car out. It's a sliding block puzzle."},{"time":364000,"text":"It's made by the company Think Fun."},{"time":366000,"text":"It's done very well. I love this puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"Well, let's play one. Here. So, here is a very simple puzzle."},{"time":371000,"text":"Well, that's too simple, let's add another piece."},{"time":373000,"text":"Okay, so how would you solve this one?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Well, move the blue one out of the way."},{"time":377000,"text":"Here, let's make it a little harder. Still pretty easy."},{"time":379000,"text":"Now we'll make it harder, a little harder."},{"time":382000,"text":"Now, this one is a little bit trickier."},{"time":384000,"text":"You know? What do you do here?"},{"time":386000,"text":"The first move is going to be what?"},{"time":388000,"text":"You're going to move the blue one up in order to get the lavender one to the right."},{"time":392000,"text":"And you can make puzzles like this one that aren't solvable at all."},{"time":395000,"text":"Those four are locked in a pinwheel; you can't get them apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"I wanted to make a sequel."},{"time":399000,"text":"I didn't come up with the original idea. But this is another way"},{"time":401000,"text":"I work as an inventor is to create a sequel."},{"time":404000,"text":"I came up with this. This is Railroad Rush Hour."},{"time":406000,"text":"It's the same basic game except I introduced a new piece,"},{"time":409000,"text":"a square piece that can move both horizontally and vertically."},{"time":412000,"text":"In the other game the cars can only move forward and back."},{"time":415000,"text":"Created a whole bunch of levels for it."},{"time":418000,"text":"Now I'm making it available to schools."},{"time":420000,"text":"And it includes exercises that show you"},{"time":422000,"text":"not just how to solve these puzzles,"},{"time":424000,"text":"but how to extract the principles that will let you solve"},{"time":427000,"text":"mathematical puzzles or problems in science, other areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"So, I'm really interested in you learning how to make your own puzzles"},{"time":434000,"text":"as well as just me creating them."},{"time":436000,"text":"Garry Trudeau calls himself an investigative cartoonist."},{"time":439000,"text":"You know, he does a lot of research before he writes a cartoon."},{"time":442000,"text":"In Discover Magazine, I'm an investigative puzzle maker."},{"time":445000,"text":"I got interested in gene sequencing."},{"time":447000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, how on Earth can you come up with a sequence"},{"time":450000,"text":"of the base pairs in DNA?\""},{"time":453000,"text":"Cut up the DNA, you sequence individual pieces,"},{"time":455000,"text":"and then you look for overlaps,"},{"time":457000,"text":"and you basically match them at the edges. And I said,"},{"time":459000,"text":"\"This is kind of like a jigsaw puzzle, except the pieces overlap.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"So, here is what I created for Discover Magazine."},{"time":465000,"text":"And it has to be solvable in a magazine."},{"time":467000,"text":"You know, you can't cut out the pieces and move them around."},{"time":469000,"text":"So, here is the nine pieces. And you're supposed to put them into this grid."},{"time":474000,"text":"And you have to choose pieces that overlap on the edge."},{"time":477000,"text":"There is only one solution. It's not that hard."},{"time":479000,"text":"But it takes some persistence."},{"time":481000,"text":"And when you're done, it makes this design,"},{"time":483000,"text":"which, if you squint, is the word \"helix.\""},{"time":488000,"text":"So, that's the form of the puzzle coming out of the content,"},{"time":491000,"text":"rather than the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"Here is a couple more. Here is a physics-based puzzle."},{"time":496000,"text":"Which way will these fall?"},{"time":498000,"text":"One of these weighs 50 pounds, 30 pounds and 10 pounds."},{"time":501000,"text":"And depending on which one weighs which amount,"},{"time":503000,"text":"they'll fall different directions."},{"time":505000,"text":"And here is a puzzle based on color mixing."},{"time":507000,"text":"I separated this image into cyan, magenta, yellow, black,"},{"time":510000,"text":"the basic printing colors, and then mixed up the separations,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and you get these peculiar pictures."},{"time":514000,"text":"Which separations were mixed up to make those pictures?"},{"time":517000,"text":"Gets you thinking about color."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Finally, what I'm doing now. So, ShuffleBrain.com,"},{"time":522000,"text":"website you can go visit, I joined up with my wife, Amy-Jo Kim."},{"time":526000,"text":"She could easily be up here giving a talk about her work."},{"time":529000,"text":"So, we're making smart games for social media."},{"time":531000,"text":"I'll explain what that means. We're looking at three trends."},{"time":535000,"text":"This is what's going on in the games industry right now."},{"time":538000,"text":"First of all, you know, for a long time"},{"time":541000,"text":"computer games meant things like \"Doom,\""},{"time":543000,"text":"where you're going around shooting things, very violent games, very fast,"},{"time":546000,"text":"aimed at teenage boys. Right? That's who plays computer games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"Well, guess what? That's changing."},{"time":551000,"text":"\"Bejeweled\" is a big hit. It was the game that really broke open"},{"time":553000,"text":"what's called casual games."},{"time":556000,"text":"And the main players are over 35, and are female."},{"time":560000,"text":"Then recently \"Rock Band\" has been a big hit."},{"time":562000,"text":"And it's a game you play with other people."},{"time":564000,"text":"It's very physical. It looks nothing like a traditional game."},{"time":567000,"text":"This is what's becoming the dominant form of electronic gaming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"Now, within that there is some interesting things happening."},{"time":573000,"text":"There is also a trend towards games that are good for you."},{"time":576000,"text":"Why? Well, we aging Boomers,"},{"time":578000,"text":"Baby Boomers, we're eating our healthy food,"},{"time":581000,"text":"we're exercising. What about our minds?"},{"time":583000,"text":"Oh no, our parents are getting Alzheimer's. We better do something."},{"time":587000,"text":"Turns out doing crossword puzzles can stave off some of the effects of Alzheimer's."},{"time":591000,"text":"So, we got games like \"Brain Age\" coming out for the Nintendo DS, huge hit."},{"time":596000,"text":"A lot of people do Sudoku. In fact some doctors prescribe it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"And then there is social media, and what's happening on the Internet."},{"time":603000,"text":"Everybody now considers themselves a creator,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and not just a viewer."},{"time":608000,"text":"And what does this add up to?"},{"time":610000,"text":"Here is what we see coming."},{"time":612000,"text":"It's games that fit into a healthy lifestyle."},{"time":615000,"text":"They're part of your life. They're not necessarily a separate thing."},{"time":618000,"text":"And they are both, something that is good for you, and they're fun."},{"time":621000,"text":"I'm a puzzle guy. My wife is an expert in social media."},{"time":624000,"text":"And we decided to combine our skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626000,"text":"Our first game is called \"Photo Grab.\" The game takes about a minute and 20 seconds."},{"time":629000,"text":"This is your first time playing my game. Okay."},{"time":631000,"text":"Let's see how well we can do. There are three images."},{"time":634000,"text":"And we have 24 seconds each."},{"time":636000,"text":"Where is that?"},{"time":638000,"text":"I'll play as fast as I can."},{"time":640000,"text":"But if you can see it, shout out the answer."},{"time":643000,"text":"You get more -- Down, okay, yeah where is that?"},{"time":646000,"text":"Oh, yeah. There, okay. J-O and --"},{"time":650000,"text":"I guess that's that part. We got the bow. That bow helps."},{"time":653000,"text":"That's his hair. You get a lot of figure-ground problems."},{"time":656000,"text":"Yeah, that one is easy. Okay. So, ahhh! Okay on to the next one."},{"time":661000,"text":"Okay, so that's the lens."},{"time":663000,"text":"Anybody?"},{"time":665000,"text":"Looks like a black shape. So, where is that?"},{"time":668000,"text":"That's the corner of the whole thing."},{"time":671000,"text":"Yeah, I've played this image before,"},{"time":673000,"text":"but even when I make up my own puzzles --"},{"time":675000,"text":"and you can put your own images in here."},{"time":677000,"text":"And we have people all over the world doing that now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681000,"text":"There we are. Visit ShuffleBrain.com"},{"time":683000,"text":"if you want to try it yourself. Thank you."},{"time":685000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}